If you use the first order Euler scheme, try to use a CFL number less 
than 2.0 and preferably in the order of 0.6-0.9, this is in order to keep 
temporal diffusion to a minimum.
Note!!!: Yes, numerical diffusion also applies in time.
source: WolfDynamics "supplement_tipsandtricks" 
https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&source=web&rct=j&opi=89978449&url=https://www.wolfdynamics.com/training/introOF8/supplement_tipsandtricks.pdf
*/

